-- Top Seeds Baylor, Stanford Advance to NCAA Women’s Final Four
-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 2012-03-27T04:31:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-27/top-seeds-baylor-stanford-advance-to-ncaa-women-s-final-four.html
Top-seeded Baylor University
advanced to the Final Four of the National Collegiate Athletic
Association women’s basketball tournament with a 77-58 rout of
the University of  Tennessee .  Brittney Griner had 23 points, 15 rebounds and nine blocked
shots yesterday in Des Moines, Iowa, as Baylor improved to 38-0
on the season.  Baylor will face fellow No. 1 regional seed Stanford in the
national semifinals on April 1 in Denver.  The Cardinal reached the Final Four with an 81-69 victory
against Duke University in Fresno, California. Nnemkadi Ogwumike
had 29 points and nine rebounds for Stanford, while her younger
sister, Chiney Ogwumike, had 12 points and 17 rebounds (35-1).  Two more No. 1 regional seeds can advance to the Final Four
today. Notre Dame faces second-seeded Maryland at the regional
final in Raleigh,  North Carolina , and Connecticut plays No. 2
 Kentucky  at the final in Kingston, Rhode Island.  The national championship game is scheduled for April 3.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Matuszewski in New York at 
